"a.易弯的，柔软的 【英】 adj. 易弯的，柔软的(supp le enough to bend freely; ductile) 【考】 palpable : touch / pliable : mold(可触摸的可以触摸到 /易变形的可以塑造)static : movable / pliable : inflexible(反义: 静态对移动/柔软对僵 硬)反义词：rigid(僵硬 的) 【例】 The sheet of plastic becomes very pliable when it is warmed. adj. 易弯的 = ductile; 易受影响的; 温顺的 = adaptable = tractable 【记】源于: pliant = pliable(pli = ply弯) 【参】liable(adj 有责任的; 有...倾向的); labile(adj 易发生变化的)以上词都来自lab化学实验室中易变的药物. 【类】palpable: touch = pliable: mold可触摸的可以触摸到 = 易变形的可以塑造static: movable = pliable: inflexible静态的不是移动的 = 柔软的不是僵硬的『pliable: influenced = censorious: condemn』『易受影响的: 影响 = 批判的: 责备』词性不符 【反】rigid(adj 刚硬的; 严格的); pertinacious = obdurate(adj 固执的); difficult to crumble(不易碎的) 【记】ply 折，弯 + able；comply 顺从，就是柔顺的 【相关】apply 应用，适用，comply 顺从, 遵守，supple 柔软的, 顺从的 pliable (adj.)  late 14c., from Old French ploiable ""flexible, bendable,"" from plier ""to bend"" (see ply (n.)). Related: Pliably, pliability."
